Giordani Says Fonden Received $81.1 Billion Since Creation

-- B y   C o r i n a   R o d r i g u e z   P o n s
-- 
2011-10-20T16:33:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/giordani-says-fonden-received-81-1-billion-since-creation.html
Venezuela ’s Finance Minister  Jorge
Giordani  said the government’s off-budget fund known as Fonden
has received $81.1 billion dollars since it was created.  About $47.3 billion have already been spent while a further
$31.9 have been assigned to projects, Giordani said today in
Caracas during the presentation of the country’s 2012 budget.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Charlie Devereux at 
 cdevereux3@bloomberg.net  